<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="sl">01 · Why outdoor refrigeration costs more</p>
    <h2>Different service environment, different parts pipeline.</h2>
    <p>Outdoor refrigerators face conditions indoor units never see: 100°F+ ambient on inland summer afternoons, salt air corrosion within 5 miles of the coast, marine layer condensation overnight, and direct sun load on east-facing built-ins. Components engineered for indoor 65 to 75°F service do not last in this environment. The labor rates and service intervals reflect this.</p>
    <p>The $120 outdoor commercial-tier diagnostic covers EPA 608 refrigerant verification, condenser fan amp test, door gasket compression check, and evaporator drain inspection. Most service calls resolve at this visit; about 30% need follow-up parts.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LABOR RATES TABLE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="sl">02 · Outdoor refrigerator labor rates</p>
    <h2>What outdoor refrigerator repair labor costs in Los Angeles.</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Labor Cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic (outdoor commercial-tier)</td><td>$120, applied to repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$220 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket replacement</td><td>$260 to $440</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator drain clearing (clogged)</td><td>$180 to $280</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Defrost heater replacement</td><td>$280 to $440</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thermostat or thermistor replacement</td><td>$220 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door hinge replacement (per side)</td><td>$240 to $380</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Refrigerant leak repair plus recharge (R-134a or R-600a)</td><td>$540 to $880</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement plus refrigerant charge</td><td>$880 to $1,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sub-Zero outdoor sealed-system repair (premium)</td><td>$680 to $1,800</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Built-in extraction and reinstall labor uplift</td><td>+$180 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Coastal corrosion service (annual)</td><td>$220 to $380</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p style="margin-top:16px;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);">All prices labor only. Parts quoted separately after diagnosis. OEM parts used wherever available. 90-day warranty on parts and labor.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 BRAND BREAKDOWN -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="sl">03 · Brand-specific cost notes</p>
    <h2>Outdoor refrigerator brands serviced in SoCal.</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Sub-Zero outdoor (UC-15IO, UC-24RO, etc.).</strong> Premium tier. Authorized service through Sub-Zero Group. Heavy-duty sealed system designed for outdoor service; longer service life (12 to 15 years typical) but premium parts pricing. $680 to $1,800 typical for sealed-system work.</li>
      <li><strong>U-Line outdoor (Echelon, Wine Captain).</strong> Whirlpool family. Mid-premium tier. Good outdoor engineering with moderate parts cost. $260 to $560 typical service calls.</li>
      <li><strong>Perlick outdoor (Signature Series).</strong> Independent Wisconsin family-owned since 1917. Pro-tier bar refrigeration. Built for high-volume operations; survives outdoor service well. $340 to $680 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Marvel outdoor.</strong> Whirlpool family. Mid-tier. Common in mid-range outdoor kitchens. $260 to $480 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Lynx outdoor refrigeration.</strong> Independent (Compton, CA). Pairs with Lynx grills. Engineered for outdoor service from inception. $340 to $680 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Hestan outdoor.</strong> Premium. Pairs with Hestan grills. Authorized service through Hestan Commercial.</li>
      <li><strong>Viking outdoor.</strong> Middleby brand. Outdoor variants of Viking residential refrigeration; not always as well-suited to outdoor as purpose-built units.</li>
      <li><strong>True residential outdoor.</strong> True Manufacturing's residential outdoor line (distinct from True commercial). Heavy-duty, parts pipeline through True commercial channel.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 COASTAL SALT AIR -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="sl">04 · Coastal salt air angle</p>
    <h2>Why Malibu, Newport, Manhattan Beach service costs more over time.</h2>
    <p>Coastal outdoor refrigerators see condenser fan motor failures at year 4 to 6 versus year 8 to 12 inland. Salt deposits on aluminum condenser fins reduce heat exchange efficiency, forcing the compressor to work harder. Door gasket compounds harden faster from UV plus salt exposure.</p>
    <p>Common pattern by location:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Within 1 mile of ocean</strong> (Malibu PCH, Newport Coast, Manhattan Beach Strand): condenser failures year 4 to 6, gasket compression year 5 to 7.</li>
      <li><strong>1 to 5 miles inland</strong> (Pacific Palisades, Hermosa, Newport inland): year 6 to 9 condenser, year 7 to 9 gasket.</li>
      <li><strong>5+ miles inland</strong> (Beverly Hills, Calabasas, Encino): year 10+ on both.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Annual coastal corrosion service ($220 to $380) at year 3 typically extends component life 2 to 4 years. We schedule preventive visits for clients on coastal installations.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 REPAIR VS REPLACE -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="sl">05 · Repair vs replace</p>
    <h2>When repair makes sense, when it doesn't.</h2>
    <p><strong>Year 0 to 7:</strong> any failure, repair. Parts cost reasonable, unit value high.</p>
    <p><strong>Year 8 to 12:</strong> case-by-case. Compressor replacement on a $2,000 mid-tier unit at year 11 is a tough call; on a $6,000 Sub-Zero outdoor it is a clear repair.</p>
    <p><strong>Year 12+:</strong> usually replace on mid-tier (U-Line, Marvel). Premium tier (Sub-Zero outdoor, Perlick) repair often still justified through year 15 because cabinet integration replacement cost exceeds repair cost.</p>
    <p>The 50% rule applies: if total repair cost exceeds 50% of comparable new unit cost, replace. For built-in luxury units the calculation includes cabinet refit cost ($2,000 to $5,000) which usually pushes the math toward repair.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 FAQ -->
<section class="section">
